main_text: 『松蓋祭り』を開始したばかりですが、本日5/10からは『愛鳥週間』ということで、今週は愛鳥週間前に毎年放鳥が行われる『キジ』の蓋を『特別雉蓋強化週間』として大特集しちゃうぜ！先日出した土山の色蓋を捕捉した時にコチラの色蓋もやっと捕捉できたので紹介。今年も♂キジの『ケ〜ン！ケ〜ン！』というけたたましい啼き聲が聞こえる季節となり、今の時期にはもってこいの蓋だね！旧秦荘町(愛荘町)の蓋です。つがいと思われる♂♀の町の鳥＊キジと町の木＊ウバメガシ、町の花＊ツツジの定番の町のシンボル3點セットと上部には蓋の曲線に合わせて曲がった稻穗と麦も描かれている。背景には町章が大きくカッコよく描かれており、立体感もあって素晴らしいデザインだ。或る施設で展示されていた展示蓋の説明プレートによると、稻穗と麦は豐かな郷土を表現し、背景の大きな町章は町の限りない發展を表現しているそうだ。此の蓋のキジはかなりカラフルな色で描かれているが、左の♀の方は實際にはもっと地味な色をしている。♂に關しても此のカラーリングだと普通のキジというよりはコウライキジっぽい氣もする。近年は移入されたコウライキジとキジの交雜した個体が増えているようなので、此の蓋のキジは其の交雜個体なのかもしれない。さて、愛鳥週間は『バードウイーク』とも呼ばれる『野鳥保護思想普及』の爲の1週間(5/10〜16)だ。當初は『バードデー』として4/10に設定されたようだが、特に野鳥を保護すべきエリアでは雪に閉ざされている所も多い爲、此の時期の『バードウイーク』に變化したらしい。此の時期の直前にキジなどの養殖された鳥の放鳥が行われるが、放鳥される鳥だけの保護を啓蒙しているわけではない。ちなみに放鳥されたキジの生存確率は1割以下らしい。マンホールに描かれるモノは環境保全啓發ネタが多いので、皆さんも此の『愛鳥週間』に野鳥の描かれた蓋を愛でてみてはいかがでしょうか？そんなわけで1枚目が先日支所の入口付近で捕捉した念願の色蓋だ。實は此處には2年前にも來ており、結構探したのだが此の蓋は『神隱し』されたかのように見つけることができなかった。不思議なこともあるものだ。2枚目は『四大聖地』の一つで滋賀県流域下水道のアレの札所である『淡海環境プラザ』の展示室にある展示蓋で、2016年10月にウチの1stインスペクターのアノ漢がマンホールナイトの發表の爲の資料集めという名目で獨自に血行した『取材の旅〜西日本篇〜』で捉えたモノだ。同じ展示蓋は實は別の施設でも展示されており、其れが3枚目だ。コチラは蓋の説明のプレートも付いている。さて此處までの色蓋は知っている人も多いと思うが、4枚目の長島鋳物特製臺座付きの展示蓋を捕捉している人はほぼいないと思う。5枚目の中型の長島臺座付きは秦荘支所内で普通に展示されているので捕捉している人も多いと思う。『小さいのがあるなら大きいのもあるはずだ』と思い調査したところ、やはり大きいのもあったわけだ。そんなわけで、秦荘の展示蓋は少なくとも3枚は製造されたことになる。6枚目は秦荘支所の駐車場にある5枚目と同じサイズの色蓋だ。此のサイズだと上下の蝶番と鍵穴が無いので町章の四方の先端がしっかり見えるようになっていて手裏劍のようでカッコイイ。大型のモノと比べるとキジの羽や稻穗や麦の實の部分が少なくなっている點も違いと云える。7枚目のノンカラーは先日、目賀田城攻略時に捕捉したモノだが、雨が降っていたのと急いでいたのであまり綺麗に仕上げることはできなかった。最後に『キジ』の寫真(8枚目)も載せておくぜ！コチラは去年函館市のP蓋のそばの飼育施設で撮ったモノだ。日本固有種であるキジではなく外來種のコウライキジになる。但しコウライキジはキジが生息しない北海道や対馬には古くから移入されており、対馬市では市の鳥にもなっている。#日本 #japan#滋賀県 #滋賀 #shiga #愛荘町 #愛荘 #秦荘#展示蓋 #雉蓋 #米蓋 #麦蓋 #躑躅系蓋 #木の実蓋 #滋賀蓋#関西の蓋百選#マンホール #manhole#キジ #pheasant#米 #rice #麦 #wheat #azalea#今日の蓋 #愛鳥週間 #birdweek#長島鋳物#獅虎連
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "shikoren450"  "comment_text": "『松蓋祭り』を開始したばかりですが、本日5/10からは『愛鳥週間』ということで、今週は愛鳥週間前に毎年放鳥が行われる『キジ』の蓋を『特別雉蓋強化週間』として大特集しちゃうぜ！

先日出した土山の色蓋を捕捉した時にコチラの色蓋もやっと捕捉できたので紹介。

今年も♂キジの『ケ〜ン！ケ〜ン！』というけたたましい啼き聲が聞こえる季節となり、今の時期にはもってこいの蓋だね！

旧秦荘町(愛荘町)の蓋です。

つがいと思われる♂♀の町の鳥＊キジと町の木＊ウバメガシ、町の花＊ツツジの定番の町のシンボル3點セットと上部には蓋の曲線に合わせて曲がった稻穗と麦も描かれている。

背景には町章が大きくカッコよく描かれており、立体感もあって素晴らしいデザインだ。

或る施設で展示されていた展示蓋の説明プレートによると、稻穗と麦は豐かな郷土を表現し、背景の大きな町章は町の限りない發展を表現しているそうだ。

此の蓋のキジはかなりカラフルな色で描かれているが、左の♀の方は實際にはもっと地味な色をしている。

♂に關しても此のカラーリングだと普通のキジというよりはコウライキジっぽい氣もする。
近年は移入されたコウライキジとキジの交雜した個体が増えているようなので、此の蓋のキジは其の交雜個体なのかもしれない。

さて、愛鳥週間は『バードウイーク』とも呼ばれる『野鳥保護思想普及』の爲の1週間(5/10〜16)だ。
當初は『バードデー』として4/10に設定されたようだが、特に野鳥を保護すべきエリアでは雪に閉ざされている所も多い爲、此の時期の『バードウイーク』に變化したらしい。

此の時期の直前にキジなどの養殖された鳥の放鳥が行われるが、放鳥される鳥だけの保護を啓蒙しているわけではない。

ちなみに放鳥されたキジの生存確率は1割以下らしい。

マンホールに描かれるモノは環境保全啓發ネタが多いので、皆さんも此の『愛鳥週間』に野鳥の描かれた蓋を愛でてみてはいかがでしょうか？

そんなわけで1枚目が先日支所の入口付近で捕捉した念願の色蓋だ。

實は此處には2年前にも來ており、結構探したのだが此の蓋は『神隱し』されたかのように見つけることができなかった。不思議なこともあるものだ。

2枚目は『四大聖地』の一つで滋賀県流域下水道のアレの札所である『淡海環境プラザ』の展示室にある展示蓋で、2016年10月にウチの1stインスペクターのアノ漢がマンホールナイトの發表の爲の資料集めという名目で獨自に血行した『取材の旅〜西日本篇〜』で捉えたモノだ。

同じ展示蓋は實は別の施設でも展示されており、其れが3枚目だ。
コチラは蓋の説明のプレートも付いている。

さて此處までの色蓋は知っている人も多いと思うが、4枚目の長島鋳物特製臺座付きの展示蓋を捕捉している人はほぼいないと思う。

5枚目の中型の長島臺座付きは秦荘支所内で普通に展示されているので捕捉している人も多いと思う。

『小さいのがあるなら大きいのもあるはずだ』と思い調査したところ、やはり大きいのもあったわけだ。

そんなわけで、秦荘の展示蓋は少なくとも3枚は製造されたことになる。

6枚目は秦荘支所の駐車場にある5枚目と同じサイズの色蓋だ。
此のサイズだと上下の蝶番と鍵穴が無いので町章の四方の先端がしっかり見えるようになっていて手裏劍のようでカッコイイ。

大型のモノと比べるとキジの羽や稻穗や麦の實の部分が少なくなっている點も違いと云える。

7枚目のノンカラーは先日、目賀田城攻略時に捕捉したモノだが、雨が降っていたのと急いでいたのであまり綺麗に仕上げることはできなかった。

最後に『キジ』の寫真(8枚目)も載せておくぜ！

コチラは去年函館市のP蓋のそばの飼育施設で撮ったモノだ。

日本固有種であるキジではなく外來種のコウライキジになる。

但しコウライキジはキジが生息しない北海道や対馬には古くから移入されており、対馬市では市の鳥にもなっている。

main_text: This is how Ukrainian fields should look like. And they were like that until the rockets of russian flew into them. But everything will definitely return to its place and there will be a clear blue sky and golden fields 🇺🇦* * *In the distance I will go beyond the village where the wheat field is spread out. The heart is constricted brought together because destiny is connected with this field. This love for the earth was given to me by my mother. I walk on the stubble as if on wings in this field. I will pluck the spikelet and look at it slowly. I'll take it with me and he'll tickle his palms. It is time to reap: to hear the roar of harvesters in the field. And the grain in the yards is filled up in the storerooms. There will be bread on the table and cakes and holy burnt loaf. Let the wheat grow in the field in the village. (Olga Kalina)°°°°°°°#insearchofmeaning👣 #паляниця #україна #українапонадусе #поле #хліб #bread #ukraine #field #cornfield #village #farmer #farm #wheat #life #villagelife #crop #nature #naturephotography #naturelover #naturephoto #photographer #photography

main_text: My heart has been broken for the people of Ukraine.My people.I am proud to be half Ukrainian. 🇺🇦🤍My grandfather escaped to America when he was young. He sought freedom and a better life for his family. And here I am 70+ years later reaping the benefits of his selfless pursuit.I am free my children are free and the homeland from which my ancestors came—and where some are still living—is a place worthy of escape even today.Life is heavy.The world is broken.My heart hurts.Will you pray with me for the people of Ukraine?My people.For safety comfort justice mercy and peace.On behalf of the beautiful people of Ukraine let us pray.-MM#mindfulmotherhood #mindfulmotherhoodpodcast #graphicdesign #digitalart #digital #art #design #watercolor #Ukraine #Ukrainian #proudukrainian #pride #europe #european #american #flower #flowers #sunflower #wheat #breadbasketofeurope #heritage #ancestor #ancestry #immigration #deargod #letuspray #prayforukraine #pray #amen
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "maggiemetz"  "comment_text": "My heart has been broken for the people of Ukraine.
My people.

I am proud to be half Ukrainian. 🇺🇦🤍

My grandfather escaped to America when he was young. He sought freedom and a better life for his family. And here I am 70+ years later reaping the benefits of his selfless pursuit.

I am free  my children are free  and the homeland from which my ancestors came—and where some are still living—is a place worthy of escape even today.

Life is heavy.
The world is broken.
My heart hurts.

Will you pray with me for the people of Ukraine?
My people.

For safety  comfort  justice  mercy  and peace.

On behalf of the beautiful people of Ukraine  let us pray.

-MM

main_text: Frey Ranch Straight Bourbon Whiskey.This whiskey is entirely made on Frey Ranch in the Sierra Nevada Watershed. The ranch has been tended to by that same family for 165 years. The generational knowledge of the land ensures that the four slow grown grains they grow create the best whiskey possible.The mash bill is comprised of non-gmo corn winter cereal rye winter wheat and two-row barley. Bottled at 90 proof.We hope to collaborate on a single barrel store pick with this amazing whiskey company!#sierranevada #whiskey #farm #familyfarm #farmtoglass #fourgrains #wheat #corn #barley #rye #liquor #liquorstore #sellwoodmoreland #pdx

main_text: 🌱 It’s time to plant cover crops at Noble ranches.On Red River Ranch our wheat pasture is already to a head. We are quickly grazing cattle on these fields to trample down the wheat. This adds great cover for the soil while putting the nutrients and wheat seed back in the ground.➡️ Scroll to see how we are tackling this issue at our grazing facility (which currently has no cattle due to a research project). This equipment is knocking down the wheat to mimic cattle trampling. Then behind him no-till cover crops are going in.This cover crop mix includes:✔️ Sunflower✔️ Various Millet✔️ Cowpeas✔️ Gourd Mix✔️ Various Sorghum✔️ Soybeans✔️ Forage Collards✔️ Various Radish✔️ Sudangrass✔️ And More!Are you planting cover crops this summer? Everyone's mix is different for their area and needs. Drop a comment of what your mix includes ⬇️
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "nobleresearchinstitute"  "comment_text": "🌱 It’s time to plant cover crops at Noble ranches.

On Red River Ranch  our wheat pasture is already to a head. We are quickly grazing cattle on these fields to trample down the wheat. This adds great cover for the soil while putting the nutrients and wheat seed back in the ground.

➡️ Scroll to see how we are tackling this issue at our grazing facility (which currently has no cattle due to a research project). This equipment is knocking down the wheat to mimic cattle trampling. Then  behind him  no-till cover crops are going in.

This cover crop mix includes:

main_text: #Mozambique: STEMA to rehabilitate grain handling equipment – AIMThe Matola Grain Silos and Terminal Company (STEMA) in Maputo province hopes to invest about 14 million dollars in rehabilitating its equipment so that it can increase its grain handling capacity.“To achieve this goal we shall resort to the banks and to our partners” said the STEMA chairperson Arlindo Chilundo at a press conference on Monday shortly after a visit to the company’s premises by the Plan and Budget Commission (CPO) of the Mozambican parliament the Assembly of the Republic.(...)He added that STEMA still has enough space to meet the demand for grain imports from all the milling companies in southern Mozambique. “We’ve been working with all the importers” he said. “STEMA does not buy the products directly. It just manages the bulk grain unloaded from the ships which is later picked up by the buyers”.He warned that the price of wheat will continue to rise on the international market because of Russia’s war against Ukraine (between them the two countries used to account for about 40 per cent of all wheat exports). One shipload of wheat arrived last week and two other ships are due to arrive before the end of May.“Channelling this wheat to the market will depend on the flexibility of the milling companies in replenishing their stocks as quickly as possible so that the price of bread does not rise too much” he said.The wheat arriving in Mozambique this month was harvested before the Russian invasion of Ukraine but Chilundo said the price was already oscillating since the demand for wheat was outstripping the supply.The full impact of the Ukraine war would not be felt until next year. Chiludo said that because of the war which has led to the closure of Ukraine’s Black Sea ports Ukraine’s wheat exports will decline while international sanctions will limit how much Russia can put on the world market.(...)READ ALL:https://buff.ly/3M1nznSSource: AIM#Mocambique #Wheat #Ukraine #SADC #Africa
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "clubofmozambique"  "comment_text": "#Mozambique: STEMA to rehabilitate grain handling equipment – AIM

The Matola Grain Silos and Terminal Company (STEMA)  in Maputo province  hopes to invest about 14 million dollars in rehabilitating its equipment so that it can increase its grain handling capacity.

“To achieve this goal  we shall resort to the banks and to our partners”  said the STEMA chairperson  Arlindo Chilundo  at a press conference on Monday  shortly after a visit to the company’s premises by the Plan and Budget Commission (CPO) of the Mozambican parliament  the Assembly of the Republic.

(...)
He added that STEMA still has enough space to meet the demand for grain imports from all the milling companies in southern Mozambique. “We’ve been working with all the importers”  he said. “STEMA does not buy the products directly. It just manages the bulk grain unloaded from the ships  which is later picked up by the buyers”.

He warned that the price of wheat will continue to rise on the international market because of Russia’s war against Ukraine (between them  the two countries used to account for about 40 per cent of all wheat exports). One shipload of wheat arrived last week  and two other ships are due to arrive before the end of May.

“Channelling this wheat to the market will depend on the flexibility of the milling companies in replenishing their stocks as quickly as possible  so that the price of bread does not rise too much”  he said.

The wheat arriving in Mozambique this month was harvested before the Russian invasion of Ukraine  but Chilundo said the price was already oscillating since the demand for wheat was outstripping the supply.

The full impact of the Ukraine war would not be felt until next year. Chiludo said that because of the war  which has led to the closure of Ukraine’s Black Sea ports  Ukraine’s wheat exports will decline  while international sanctions will limit how much Russia can put on the world market.
(...)

main_text: 【放空耍廢金門行】我沒想過這系列可以這麼多照片誒哈哈哈哈哈但金門真的很好玩以及很好拍！@moniichen13 早一天先到，找大片未收割的麥田找很辛苦；殊不知...之後不用特別找都有看到！就是人說的莫非定律啊！於是，在半路上看到這一大片的麥田，就路邊臨時停車衝進去。真的走很小心怕踩了農夫的心血。然後長得高高的麥子，讓我們一邊走一邊尖叫也一邊被刺🤣🤣🤣好看照片的背後都有著堅強的故事！#kinmen #kinmentravel #friends #vocation #wheat #wheatfield #cheongsam #金門景點 #金門旅遊 #ig打卡景點
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "immerbeimir"  "comment_text": "【放空耍廢金門行】

我沒想過這系列可以這麼多照片誒哈哈哈哈哈
但金門真的很好玩以及很好拍！

@moniichen13 早一天先到，找大片未收割的麥田找很辛苦；殊不知...之後不用特別找都有看到！就是人說的莫非定律啊！

於是，在半路上看到這一大片的麥田，就路邊臨時停車衝進去。

然後長得高高的麥子，讓我們一邊走一邊尖叫也一邊被刺🤣🤣🤣

好看照片的背後都有著堅強的故事！

comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "_namdar_"  "comment_text": "🇱🇧 Tabouli - تبوله
+Recipe
بلغور گندم 100-150g
جعفری 300g
نعنا 30g-⅒جعفری
گوجه نگینی 100g
لیمو ترش 2 عدد
پیازچه 2 شاخه
روغن زیتون 100-150g
فلفل سیاه به اندازه دلخواه
نمک به اندازه
طرز تهیه: آب را بگذارید جوش بیاید و سپس بلغور را در آب ریخته و سریعا حرارت زیر آب را خاموش کنید و اجازه دهید با پایین آمدن دمای آب،بلغور نرم شود.
پیازچه اسلایس حلقه ای شود.
جعفری و نعنا باهم کاملا خرد شود.
گوجه ی نگینی و بقیه ی مواد را مخلوط کرده و در آخر نمک و فلفل و لیمو ترش و روغن زیتون را افزوده و طعم را تنظیم کنید.
+🫓☘️میتوان آن را با نان پیتا،ادویه پولبیبر و میکرو گرین های مختلف گارنیش کرد.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Bulgur-Wheat semolina 100-150g
Parsley 300g
Mint 30g-⅒ parsley
Dicing Tomato 100g
2 Lemons
Scallion-green onion 2 branches
Olive oil 100-150g
Black pepper as desired
As much salt
Preparation: Let the water boil and then pour the semolina in the water and immediately turn off the heat under the water and let the semolina soften as the water temperature drops.
Slice the greenonion into rings.
Finely chop the parsley and mint.
Mix the tomatoes and the rest of the ingredients  and finally add the salt  pepper lemon and olive oil and adjust the taste.
+🫓☘️It can be garnished with pita bread pul biber and microgreens.

main_text: How do you store your sourdough for the week? I’ve been enjoying my @blackanddeckerappliances electric bread knife for cutting up sourdough that’s a few days old and on the tougher side. I slice it up into individual pieces and then store it in the fridge in a Ziploc or plastic bread bag. main_text: If you your partner or one of your other children has a food allergy the thought of introducing that food to your new baby can cause some anxiety.The delay of the family member’s trigger food is not recommended. There is no evidence that delay of introduction has a protective effect on food allergies.It’s important to remember to consider the food allergic person to ensure that they remain safe during the introduction of a food that they are allergic to. Prepare/serve food on separate plates and with different cutlery than the allergic person uses.Speak with your pediatrician or allergist to see if there should be an introduction plan to move forward. This may put your mind at ease when it comes to feeding a potential allergen.Don’t introduce foods before 4 months of age and preferably around 6 months of age. This should include both top allergens food family members may be allergic to and other foods that your family eats. Of course DO NOT feed or reintroduce your baby any food you know that they already have an allergy to without supervision from an allergist.As always contact your pediatrician or dietitian for concerns about adjusting your child’s diet.#foodallergy #cmpa #food #allergy #startingsolids #solidfood #babyfoodideas #babyfood #peanut #peanutallergy #celiacdisease #wheat #dietitian #nutrition #infantnutrition #breastfeeding #breastfeed #breastfed #foodallergymom #fpies
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "bloompedsnutrition"  "comment_text": "If you  your partner  or one of your other children has a food allergy  the thought of introducing that food to your new baby can cause some anxiety.

The delay of the family member’s trigger food is not recommended. There is no evidence that delay of introduction has a protective effect on food allergies.

It’s important to remember to consider the food allergic person to ensure that they remain safe during the introduction of a food that they are allergic to. Prepare/serve food on separate plates and with different cutlery than the allergic person uses.

Speak with your pediatrician or allergist to see if there should be an introduction plan to move forward. This may put your mind at ease when it comes to feeding a potential allergen.

Don’t introduce foods before 4 months of age  and preferably around 6 months of age. This should include both top allergens  food family members may be allergic to  and other foods that your family eats. Of course  DO NOT feed or reintroduce your baby any food you know that they already have an allergy to without supervision from an allergist.

As always  contact your pediatrician or dietitian for concerns about adjusting your child’s diet.

#foodallergy #cmpa #food #allergy #startingsolids #solidfood #babyfoodideas #babyfood #peanut #peanutallergy #celiacdisease #wheat #dietitian #nutrition #infantnutrition #breastfeeding #breastfeed #breastfed #foodallergymom #fpies"}}

main_text: Aatta Laadu.This sweet is made from whole wheat flour ghee and sugar. I have also added crushed almonds in it.Ingredients:-2 cups whole wheat flour1/2 cup sugar 1/4 cup water2 cardamoms crushedGhee- 1/2 cup + 1 tsp.1/4 cup almonds roasted and crushedMethod:-First dry roast the flour in a thick pan for 10-15 mins till it becomes light brown.In the mean while make sugar bhura- make a one string syrup using sugar and water once syrup is made add one tsp ghee and switch off flame. The sugar then turns into crystalline form.Heat ghee roast the atta in the ghee till its brown add the cardamom powder add the crushed almonds.Once done switch off flame add the sugar bura mix and make laddoos. And relish these ❤️#atta #laddo #laddoo #laddu #wheat #healthyfood #healthysweets #meetha #gharkakhaana #vegetarian #superfood #superfoods #meethai #trendingreels #recipes #recipepost #goodfood #goodmood #instafood #instagram #instagoodie #foodblogger #foodblogfeed #mumbaifoodicious #indianfood #pakistanfood
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "foodaffairby_sneha"  "comment_text": "Aatta Laadu.
This sweet is made from whole wheat flour  ghee and sugar. I have also added crushed almonds in it.
Ingredients:-
2 cups whole wheat flour
1/2 cup sugar  1/4 cup water 
2 cardamoms crushed 
Ghee- 1/2 cup + 1 tsp.
1/4 cup almonds roasted and crushed
Method:-
First dry roast the flour in a thick pan for 10-15 mins till it becomes light brown.
In the mean while make sugar bhura- make a one string syrup using sugar and water  once syrup is made  add one tsp ghee and switch off flame. The sugar then turns into crystalline form.
Heat ghee  roast the atta in the ghee till its brown  add the cardamom powder  add the crushed almonds.
Once done  switch off flame  add the sugar bura mix and make laddoos. And relish these ❤️

main_text: देश की सरकारी संस्थाओं द्वारा की जाने वाली गेहूं की खरीद इस चालू विपणन सत्र 2021-22 में 15 साल के निचले स्तर पर आ सकती है. इससे पहले इससे कम खरीद 2007-08 के दौरान की गई थी जो 111.28 लाख मीट्रिक टन थी. वहीं इस बार सरकार द्वारा गेहूं की खरीद का आंकड़ा 195 लाख मीट्रिक टन के आसपास ही सिमट सकता है.भारत में ज्यादातर किसान किसान अप्रैल से मई के बीच ही गेहूं को बाजार में बेचते हैं हालांकि सरकारी तकनीकी रूप से गेहूं की खरीद जून तक करती है. इसके अलावा यह पहली बार होगा कि इस साल के दौरान खरीदा गया गेहूं पिछले विपणन सीजन की शुरुआत में उपल्बध सार्वजनिक स्टॉक से कम है. भारत में हमेशा ये देखा जाता है कि नई खरीद शुरुआती उपल्बध स्टॉक से ज्यादा होती है. इससे पहले 2006-07 और 2007-08 में ऐसा हुआ था जब शुरुआती उपल्बध स्टॉक नई खरीद से कम था.पूरी खबर को पढ़ने के लिए बायो में दिये गये लिंक पर जाये.Hit the #link in #bio to read the full #article.#India #Wheat #SocialSecurity #Food #Russia #Ukraine #RussiaUkraineCrisis #Farmers #Exporthttps://www.panchayattimes.com/amid-russia-ukraine-crisis-indian-government-wheat-procurement-lowest-in-15-years-know-the-complications-of-this-in-indian-market-and-social-security/

main_text: #coeliacawarenessweek 🧡 Same post from last year with new blurry memes!!!🧡Hey everyone! I’m @elliecolts aka The Coeliac Queen ❤️#CoeliacAwarenessWeekI got diagnosed with Coeliac at 15 (I’m 23 now). It is an auto-immune disease which means my body begins to attack itself when I ingest gluten. I can’t eat gluten wheat barely rye spelt oats.I’ll go into further detail this week dispelling coeliac myths like “isn’t a little bit okay?” - NO!But I just wanted to focus on one of the biggest things I get asked which is “what happens to you if you do eat it?”I have a long list of symptoms; nausea abdominal cramps brain-fog hair loss weight fluctuation fatigue low mood dizziness mouth ulcers ‘gluten’ rash joint pain joint swelling calcium deficiency iron deficiency borderline anaemia. The most damaging in my own personal experience however is the ridiculous bloating and stomach spasms.I am a UK size 6/8 but when I get glutened my stomach expands 3X the size and is so incredibly painful hot sore hard and I don’t fit in my trousers anymore.It might seem very surface to a lot of people but this has given me body image issues. I don’t just worry about feeling ‘sick’ I worry about not fitting in my clothes. I have size 14 joggers I sit in when I’ve been glutened. There is nothing wrong with that - but when I’m usually a size 6/8 it’s a huge increase over the course of hours.Any questions anyone has about coeliac please ask away! I’ll be shining a light on the disease throughout this whole week for @coeliacuk ❤️#coeliac #coeliacdisease #celiac #celiacdisease #coeliacawarenessweek #coeliacawareness #celiacawareness #celiacawarenessmonth #glutenfree #glutenfrei #singluten #sansgluten #senzaglutine #wheat #barley #rye #oats #crosscontamination #bloating #bloated #bloatedtummy #bloatedbelly #bodyimage #bodyimageissues #bodypositivity #bodypositive #bodydysmorphia #bodydismorphia #shinealightoncoeliac
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "thecoeliacqueen"  "comment_text": "#coeliacawarenessweek 🧡 Same post from last year with new blurry memes!!!🧡

Hey everyone! I’m @elliecolts aka The Coeliac Queen ❤️

#CoeliacAwarenessWeek

I got diagnosed with Coeliac at 15 (I’m 23 now). It is an auto-immune disease which means my body begins to attack itself when I ingest gluten. I can’t eat gluten  wheat  barely  rye  spelt  oats.

I’ll go into further detail this week dispelling coeliac myths like “isn’t a little bit okay?” - NO!

But I just wanted to focus on one of the biggest things I get asked which is “what happens to you if you do eat it?”

I have a long list of symptoms; nausea  abdominal cramps  brain-fog  hair loss  weight fluctuation  fatigue  low mood  dizziness  mouth ulcers  ‘gluten’ rash  joint pain  joint swelling  calcium deficiency  iron deficiency  borderline anaemia. The most damaging in my own personal experience however is the ridiculous bloating and stomach spasms.

I am a UK size 6/8  but when I get glutened  my stomach expands 3X the size and is so incredibly painful  hot  sore  hard and I don’t fit in my trousers anymore.

It might seem very surface to a lot of people  but this has given me body image issues. I don’t just worry about feeling ‘sick’ I worry about not fitting in my clothes. I have size 14 joggers I sit in when I’ve been glutened. There is nothing wrong with that - but when I’m usually a size 6/8  it’s a huge increase over the course of hours.

Any questions anyone has about coeliac  please ask away! I’ll be shining a light on the disease throughout this whole week for @coeliacuk ❤️

{"1": {"comment_id": "thekey2deborah"  "comment_text": "☀️”Living off the Land!”🌱

To eat organically I understand can be restorative to our microbiombe and depending on our motivation there are a great variety of opportunities for us to seek better health.
Slowly my husband and I are working towards eradicating all non organic foods from our home.

This is no easy feat  as we realise some items cannot be replicated or may be difficult to source.
But perhaps trying our own version or preparing something completely new is the way to go?!

This week we made a ketchup.
The recipe slightly tweaked  (from @kilneruk) we used less sugar  more garlic  our own homemade apple cider vinegar and plenty of spice. It’s really turned out well and is very tasty.
Swipe left for the full recipe 🥫

Turmeric is a spice I want to use more of  to help with inflammation  reduce toxins  arthritic pain and more.

You do need a good quality Turmeric to be of value  it's important to have a Turmeric extract that provides a good dose of Curcumin and Black pepper.

I like to medicate naturally where possible and for this reason use whole foods  spices  herbs and aim to exercise gently along with a daily walk to aid my well-being.

🌾So back to the beautiful baking that we all collectively enjoy creating! ✨🥪🔆

I’ve used my recent purchase of Turmeric to create some wholesome loaves one with botanical golden blend and caramelised onions!” One baked in a tin  recently bought from @campbell2664 encased with a few pumpkin seeds😋

My ingredients are all whole grains  including Wholewheat  Buckwheat Barley  Rye  YQ grain and Squareheads Master.
Beautiful grains obtained through @hodmedods and @gilchesters @deliver__deli and @bakerybitsltd

🌟 👩🏻‍🍳Happy baking and cooking to all our foodie friends! 🌟 🧑🏽‍🍳

Thoughts for dear @svetpenkina 🥒 @iso_la_05 🌻💙💛🕊 and prayers for all in Ukraine 🇺🇦

Last photo ✨
See the Sparrow eating from our bird feeder 🔆
Bryan is delighted as the feeder has been hanging  waiting for the birdies for quite a while! 🌞

main_text: A meeting of the ECC presided over by Finance Minister Miftah Ismail also decided to reduce the prices of wheat sugar and vegetable oil/ghee at the outlets of Utility Stores Corporation for two months.For more head over to the link in bio or visit thediteur.com#pakistan #economic #wheat #thediteur

We aren’t talking *instagram-worthy* pictures or vital gluten or enzymes or improvers we are talking real science and art. 🧬🥖Let’s take a simple example. Different wheat beers taste different because of the variety/quality of grains as well as the fermentation processes used. Rings a bell? 🔔Why might that be?No brownie points for answering that. 🥲🤣The entire journey of the wheat grain over a period of 95-120 days from seed to harvest needs to be taken into account when you are talking about quality of a wheat flour.Nothing on this planet exists in isolation we are as interdependent and intertwined as one can be. 🌚🌝Thus Genetics (Species and Variety) Growth Environment Plant Management Post-Harvest Management Milling Technology Baking Science all play important roles in themselves to determine the quality of your end products made from wheat.You can’t get away with not knowing even one of the above. So yeah try to dig deeper when you pickup a batch of flour off the shelf or internet next time.Any doubts? ☀️🙆🏻‍♀️Ask away in the comments below.💥💥💥
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "threeonefarms"  "comment_text": "We aren’t talking *instagram-worthy* pictures or vital gluten or enzymes or improvers  we are talking real science and art. 🧬🥖

Let’s take a simple example. Different wheat beers taste different because of the variety/quality of grains as well as the fermentation processes used. Rings a bell? 🔔

Why might that be?

No brownie points for answering that. 🥲🤣

The entire journey of the wheat grain over a period of 95-120 days from seed to harvest needs to be taken into account when you are talking about quality of a wheat flour.

Nothing on this planet exists in isolation  we are as interdependent and intertwined as one can be. 🌚🌝

Thus  Genetics (Species and Variety)  Growth Environment  Plant Management  Post-Harvest Management  Milling Technology  Baking Science  all play important roles in themselves to determine the quality of your end products made from wheat.

You can’t get away with not knowing even one of the above. So  yeah  try to dig deeper when you pickup a batch of flour off the shelf or internet next time.

Any doubts? ☀️🙆🏻‍♀️

Ask away in the comments below.

main_text: I had my appointment yesterday with the child psychologist.We are offered this service through my sons allergy teamit’s just an appointment for me and I get to talk about how living with my sons allergies has a mental affect on me.There’s usually a point in these appointments where I get quite emotional.Yesterday we spoke about how I find it quite upsetting when people ask me if my son will outgrow his allergies or the famous comment “I’m sure he’ll outgrow them” I appreciate people ask these questions out of interest and not to be negative but I find them very hard.If I had a crystal ballI would love to say YEShe will outgrow them!I explained how always having to explain to people makes it hit home each time and a little piece of my heart breaks every time I’m asked these questions.Obviously our ultimate goal and wish is that he will outgrow them but as we don’t know what the future holdsI find it a really difficult question to answer.We take each day as it comesliving with his allergies and also being realistic in that he may not outgrow his allergies or all of them.Just wondering if anybody else finds these questions hard too?...#freefromlife #allergies #allergylife #milk #egg #wheat #soya #legumes #bananas #allergycooking #allergyfriendly #allergycommunity #allergyawareness #cmpa #wheatallergy #eggallergy #soyaallergy #bananaallergy #legumeallergy #allergymum
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "a_mum.a_son_and_allergies_"  "comment_text": "I had my appointment yesterday with the child psychologist.We are offered this service through my sons allergy team it’s just an appointment for me and I get to talk about how living with my sons allergies has a mental affect on me.

There’s usually a point in these appointments where I get quite emotional.Yesterday we spoke about how I find it quite upsetting when people ask me if my son will outgrow his allergies or the famous comment “I’m sure he’ll outgrow them” I appreciate people ask these questions out of interest and not to be negative but I find them very hard.If I had a crystal ball I would love to say YES he will outgrow them!I explained how always having to explain to people makes it hit home each time and a little piece of my heart breaks every time I’m asked these questions.

Obviously our ultimate goal and wish is that he will outgrow them but as we don’t know what the future holds I find it a really difficult question to answer.We take each day as it comes living with his allergies and also being realistic in that he may not outgrow his allergies or all of them.

Just wondering if anybody else finds these questions hard too?
.
.
.
#freefromlife #allergies #allergylife #milk #egg #wheat #soya #legumes #bananas #allergycooking #allergyfriendly #allergycommunity #allergyawareness #cmpa #wheatallergy #eggallergy #soyaallergy #bananaallergy #legumeallergy #allergymum"}}

この透明感に吸い込まれそうだよー( ᷇࿀ ᷆ )"}  "38": {"comment_id": "suu.nooto"  "comment_text": "@suu.nooto どうもありがとう🌱💚青麦は透明感がある色なのに、そこから出てくるエネルギーというか、パワーというか…すごいよね✨"}  "39": {"comment_id": "citron.m20"  "comment_text": "麦を見たのは半世紀も前😂なんとも言えないほど懐かしい。中に黒い炭のような麦もできるのよ。"}  "40": {"comment_id": "hidebouchan"  "comment_text": "@hidebouchan 稲や麦は何だかパワーを貰えますよね✨黒い炭のような麦ですか😮黒麦焼酎になるのかなぁ🤔🤔"}  "41": {"comment_id": "citron.m20"  "comment_text": "@citron.m20 黒くなるのは麦の病気の一種ですね。"}  "42": {"comment_id": "hidebouchan"  "comment_text": "@hidebouchan 😅😅😅🌱🌱"}}

main_text: #pcos day 8During 26 year old Manisha PCOS girl she mentioned she is only taking cucumber sprouts at night.We discussed further and realised she heard not to have wheat during PCOS.(Pulses and cereals are not compete protein but when convinced together- becomes compete)#wheat or #gluten can definitely be added in PCOS. Don’t get fooled by Instagram.Let’s get to the basics first:1. What is glutenIt’s a type of protein which helps in binding of wheat barley and rye2. Do all need to go gluten freeNo3. When to avoid wheat?If you feel vomiting or have rashes or instant loose motion. Talk to your dietitian about it.4. What are the best flours for PCOSSwipe left 😁Note:Brands shown is for easy understanding. comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "nutrbylakshita"  "comment_text": "#pcos day 8

During 26 year old Manisha PCOS girl  she mentioned she is only taking cucumber sprouts at night.

We discussed further and realised she heard not to have wheat during PCOS.

(Pulses and cereals are not compete protein  but when convinced together- becomes compete)

#wheat or #gluten can definitely be added in PCOS. Don’t get fooled by Instagram.

Let’s get to the basics first:

1. What is gluten
It’s a type of protein which helps in binding of wheat  barley and rye

2. Do all need to go gluten free
No

3. When to avoid wheat?
If you feel vomiting or have rashes or instant loose motion. Talk to your dietitian about it.

4. What are the best flours for PCOS
Swipe left 😁

Note:
Brands shown is for easy understanding. We are not suggesting any brands.

main_text: 🌱ЧУДО ПРОРОСШЕГО ЗЕРНА🌱В последние несколько лет все более модным становится добавление в еду пророщенных зёрен - спраутс.Это просто мода или в росточках действительно есть польза?Сегодня «Гаспадар» поможет Вам ответить на этот вопрос.Ростки пшеницы можно назвать эликсиром жизни. Ежедневно съедая горстку проросших зёрен вы пополните истощённые энергетические запасы организма и вдохновите его на обновление клеток.А ещё проросшие зёрна пшеницы быстро восстанавливают организм после физического истощения.Ростки пшеничных зёрен благотворно влияют на обмен веществ. Они - истинная панацея для людей с патологиями эндокринной системы (в частности с сахарным диабетом) и почечно-печёночными заболеваниями.Наукой доказано что целебные зёрнышки уравновешивают психоэмоциональное состояние человека.Для того чтобы получить спраутс Вам необходимо взять 4 столовых ложки (суточная доза на одного человека) «Пшеницы для проращивания» ТМ «Скарбонка здароуя» и тщательно промыть её проточной водой.Далее равномерным слоем (до 1 см) распределите пшеницу по фарфоровой или эмалированной посуде (не металлической) и залейте водой на уровне чуть выше верхнего слоя зерна. Ёмкость с пшеницей следует поставить в тёплое место и накрыть марлей. Главные условия при проращивании – вода доступ воздуха и тепло. На протяжении дня необходимо промывать 2-3 раза.Через 25-30 часов появятся ростки. Готовыми к употреблению считаются зернышки с "проклюнувшимися" ростками длинной 1-2 мм. но не более 3-х. Пророщенные зерна нужно хорошо промыть под струёй воды для удаления запаха после чего они готовы к употреблению.Пророщенные зёрна едят сырыми: бросьте горсточку в овощной салат – блюдо станет в разы полезнее!«Гаспадар» рекомендует начинать употребление пророщенных зёрен с одной чайной ложки в день постепенно увеличивая их количество – но не более 70 г в сутки.Хранить спраутс нужно в холодильнике не более 5 дней.#гаспадар #пшеница #мукагаспадар #пшеницадляпроращивания #зернопшеницы #спраутс #здоровоепитание #питание #здоровье #gaspadar #health #healthyfood #wheat #grain #may #spring #happy #eat
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "muka_gaspadar"  "comment_text": "🌱ЧУДО ПРОРОСШЕГО ЗЕРНА🌱

В последние несколько лет все более модным становится добавление в еду пророщенных зёрен - спраутс.
Это просто мода или в росточках действительно есть польза?

Сегодня «Гаспадар» поможет Вам ответить на этот вопрос.
Ростки пшеницы можно назвать эликсиром жизни. Ежедневно съедая горстку проросших зёрен  вы пополните истощённые энергетические запасы организма и вдохновите его на обновление клеток.

А ещё проросшие зёрна пшеницы быстро восстанавливают организм после физического истощения.
Ростки пшеничных зёрен благотворно влияют на обмен веществ. Они - истинная панацея для людей с патологиями эндокринной системы (в частности  с сахарным диабетом) и почечно-печёночными заболеваниями.

Наукой доказано  что целебные зёрнышки уравновешивают психоэмоциональное состояние человека.

Для того  чтобы получить спраутс Вам необходимо взять 4 столовых ложки (суточная доза на одного человека) «Пшеницы для проращивания» ТМ «Скарбонка здароуя» и тщательно промыть её проточной водой.
Далее  равномерным слоем (до 1 см) распределите пшеницу по фарфоровой или эмалированной посуде (не металлической) и залейте водой  на уровне чуть выше верхнего слоя зерна. Ёмкость с пшеницей следует поставить в тёплое место и накрыть марлей. Главные условия при проращивании – вода  доступ воздуха и тепло. На протяжении дня необходимо промывать 2-3 раза.
Через 25-30 часов появятся ростки. Готовыми к употреблению считаются зернышки с "проклюнувшимися" ростками длинной 1-2 мм.  но не более 3-х. Пророщенные зерна нужно хорошо промыть под струёй воды для удаления запаха  после чего они готовы к употреблению.
Пророщенные зёрна едят сырыми: бросьте горсточку в овощной салат – блюдо станет в разы полезнее!

«Гаспадар» рекомендует начинать употребление пророщенных зёрен с одной чайной ложки в день  постепенно увеличивая их количество – но не более 70 г в сутки.

Хранить спраутс нужно в холодильнике не более 5 дней.

comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "persiancookingart"  "comment_text": "ENJOY!

Ingredients:
250 g. cracked wheat
1 medium onion (grated)
2 medium carrots (diced small)
150 g. celery (chopped small)
60 g. parsley (finely chopped)
2 tsp. flour
Juice of a lemon
5 cups of water
Salt  black pepper and turmeric powder
Olive oil

Instructions:
1) Wash the cracked wheat in a large bowl and drain.
2) Heat olive oil in a pot over medium heat; sauté onion until soft.
3) Add flour  salt  pepper and turmeric.
4) Add cracked wheat  celery  carrots and water. Cover and let cook.
5) After 1 hour  add parsley and let cook for 30 minutes.
6) Add lemon juice and serve the soup immediately.

main_text: The Economic Coordination Committee (ECC) of the Cabinet has approved import of three million metric tonnes of wheat and decided to continue with the former Prime Minister’s Relief Package announced in 2020 for another two months – May and June 2022 – to provide subsidy on five essential commodities.The ECC meeting presided over by Minister for Finance and Revenue Miftah Ismail on a summary moved by the Ministry of National Food Security and Research after discussing the current world scenario as well as its effects on the world economy and demand-supply situation of wheat in the country approved three MMT of wheat import on need basis depending upon the demand of the PASSCO and provincial governments to build up strategic reserves and to stabilize wheat prices in the country.The meeting directed the concerned authorities to frame modalities for financing and procurement.#ECC #wheat #edibleitems
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "businessrecorder"  "comment_text": "The Economic Coordination Committee (ECC) of the Cabinet has approved import of three million metric tonnes of wheat and decided to continue with the former Prime Minister’s Relief Package announced in 2020 for another two months – May and June 2022 – to provide subsidy on five essential commodities.

The ECC meeting presided over by Minister for Finance and Revenue Miftah Ismail on a summary moved by the Ministry of National Food Security and Research after discussing the current world scenario  as well as  its effects on the world economy and demand-supply situation of wheat in the country  approved three MMT of wheat import on need basis  depending upon the demand of the PASSCO and provincial governments to build up strategic reserves and to stabilize wheat prices in the country.

The meeting directed the concerned authorities to frame modalities for financing and procurement.

#ECC #wheat #edibleitems"}}

main_text: Breakfast Recipes.Wheat flour + Milk Dose.Ghee smeared DosaChutney Pudi.Jaggery.Wheat dosa is soft and Yummy.How to Prepare:Wheat Flour : 2 cups.Boiled and cooled Milk : 1 Cup.Semolina Medium/ Rava : 2 tbs.Salt to tasteMix all the ingredients nicely add required water.The batter consistency is to be little thinner than normal dosa batter.Heat a pan clean with a kitchen tissue.Add a ladle of batter. Spread it slowly. (Do not press the ladle with pressure). Let the flame be low while spreading the batter. Sprinkle little oil on top of dosa.Cook on medium flameTurn the other side and cook till slightly golden brown.Take it out and serve or enjoy with your favourite side dish.Ghee or Butter is optional.If you like crispy dosa do cook completely on low flame.But it turns very hard#breakfastclub#wheat#dosalove#yummyfood😋#yummyfoods#easyrecipe#healthyeats#healthyeats#indianblogger
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "adige_by_nalini"  "comment_text": "Breakfast Recipes.
Wheat flour + Milk Dose.Ghee smeared Dosa
Chutney Pudi.
Jaggery.

Wheat dosa is soft and Yummy.
How to Prepare:
Wheat Flour : 2 cups.
Boiled and cooled Milk : 1 Cup.
Semolina Medium/ Rava : 2 tbs.
Salt to taste
Mix all the ingredients nicely add required water.
The batter consistency is to be little thinner than normal dosa batter.
Heat a pan  clean with a kitchen tissue.
Add a ladle of batter. Spread it slowly. (Do not press the ladle with pressure). Let the flame be low while spreading the batter. Sprinkle little oil on top of dosa.
Cook on medium flame
Turn the other side and cook till slightly golden brown.
Take it out and serve or enjoy with your favourite side dish.
Ghee or Butter is optional.
If you like crispy dosa do cook completely on low flame.
But it turns very hard

main_text: שניה לפני שאני מהלכת יחפה..״נעמה בואי נצטלם בחיטה.. לפני שיקצרו..״״אוף לא בא לי!!״״קניתי לך חולצה מתאימה.. כמה תמונות וזהו.״״לא רוצה את החולצה הזאת!!״מגיעים לשדה..לובשת את החולצה..״רואים לי את הבטן..זה חשוף גם למעלה..לא רוצה זה לא יפה!״בכי.. אמיתי.. עם דמעות ועיניים אדומות.. מגבונים..״טוב בואי נחזור הביתה..העיניים שלך נפוחות ורואים שאת לא רוצה..לא חייבים!״״טוב.. אני אצטלם״״הנה טוב לך??״״לא.. תחייכי..״״מממ..״אני מקליקה..״את מהממת!... איזו ילדה דוגמנית!... יופי! ככה!..״והנה היא נכנסה לדמות החייכנית..נחשו מה?היא לא רצתה ללכתוכמובן שצילמנו גם כמה קפיצות באויר ותרגילי גמישות 😅😍מה לא עושים כדי שהסנדל לא ילך יחף 🤣🤣#אמאמאוהבת #שדהחיטה #אמאצלמת #ילדהשלי#thechildrenoftheworld #children_of_the_world #wheat #צילוםאמנותי #צילוםילדים #ילדיישראל
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "limor_david_samovich_afunimstu"  "comment_text": "שניה לפני שאני מהלכת יחפה..

״נעמה  בואי נצטלם בחיטה.. לפני שיקצרו..״
״אוף  לא בא לי!!״
״קניתי לך חולצה מתאימה.. כמה תמונות וזהו.״
״לא רוצה את החולצה הזאת!!״

מגיעים לשדה..
לובשת את החולצה..
״רואים לי את הבטן..
זה חשוף גם למעלה..
לא רוצה  זה לא יפה!״

בכי.. אמיתי.. עם דמעות ועיניים אדומות.. מגבונים..

״טוב  בואי נחזור הביתה..
העיניים שלך נפוחות ורואים שאת לא רוצה..
לא חייבים!״

״טוב.. אני אצטלם״

״הנה  טוב לך??״
״לא.. תחייכי..״
״מממ..״

אני מקליקה..
״את מהממת!... איזו ילדה דוגמנית!... יופי! ככה!..״

והנה היא נכנסה לדמות החייכנית..

נחשו מה?
היא לא רצתה ללכת
וכמובן שצילמנו גם כמה קפיצות באויר ותרגילי גמישות 😅😍

מה לא עושים כדי שהסנדל לא ילך יחף 🤣🤣

main_text: A few evenings ago after taking photos of stormy skies I stopped to take a sunset photo over a wheat field south of Granger Texas. As I finished my visual wandering I met Steve a Granger-area farmer. "That's our wheat" he said. It was a quiet night giving us time to visit a few minutes. Steve mentioned recent tornados that blew through the area. His parent's home sustained damage their barn destroyed. They are okay. His father is in his 90s mother in her 80s. Photos of Steve make this post a better one. The last image shows Steve's family crops corn at left wheat on the right expressive skies overhead. Scenes from farm country on the Blackland Prairie. #wheat #farmers #blacklandprairie #inspiretexasnow #grangertexas #texasphotographer #landscape #pictorial #sunset #nikon #nikonusa

main_text: Today was an incredibly beautiful day! Every day is beautiful in its own way but I guess you could say being outside was exceptionally pleasant today. The two pictures I took are of one of our three Einkorn fields. Despite all the incredible attributes of Einkorn one of the criticisms of many cash crops wheat included (even if grown organically) is that when planted it is considered a monoculture meaning it is one species grown by itself. This may be true of conventional wheat where a pre-planting dousing with herbicides kills everything or heavy tillage for weeks is used to control young weeds. This is not the case in our Einkorn fields as you can see from the photos every gap between the Einkorn the ground is covered with dozens of different “weeds” many of which are flowering. The Einkorn outcompetes them and rises above and eventually blocks enough light to impede their growth at least until after harvesting. When standing in the fields you can hear the bees buzzing and see insects of every kind working away. It’s anything but a monoculture!

main_text: Wheat berries are the edible part of the wheat kernel before it undergoes any processing. Since the kernels are left intact nearly all the nutrients remain. comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "deviant_films"  "comment_text": "As I Walked Out One Evening

W. H. Auden 

As I walked out one evening 
   Walking down Bristol Street 
The crowds upon the pavement
   Were fields of harvest wheat.

And down by the brimming river
   I heard a lover sing
Under an arch of the railway:
   'Love has no ending.

'I'll love you  dear  I'll love you
   Till China and Africa meet 
And the river jumps over the mountain
   And the salmon sing in the street 

'I'll love you till the ocean
   Is folded and hung up to dry
And the seven stars go squawking
   Like geese about the sky.

'The years shall run like rabbits 
   For in my arms I hold
The Flower of the Ages 
   And the first love of the world.'

But all the clocks in the city
   Began to whirr and chime:
'O let not Time deceive you 
   You cannot conquer Time.

'In the burrows of the Nightmare
   Where Justice naked is 
Time watches from the shadow
   And coughs when you would kiss.

'In headaches and in worry
   Vaguely life leaks away 
And Time will have his fancy
   To-morrow or to-day.

'Into many a green valley
   Drifts the appalling snow;
Time breaks the threaded dances
   And the diver's brilliant bow.

'O plunge your hands in water 
   Plunge them in up to the wrist;
Stare  stare in the basin
   And wonder what you've missed.

'The glacier knocks in the cupboard 
   The desert sighs in the bed 
And the crack in the tea-cup opens
   A lane to the land of the dead.

'Where the beggars raffle the banknotes
   And the Giant is enchanting to Jack 
And the Lily-white Boy is a Roarer 
   And Jill goes down on her back.

'O look  look in the mirror 
   O look in your distress:
Life remains a blessing
   Although you cannot bless.

'O stand  stand at the window
   As the tears scald and start;
You shall love your crooked neighbour
   With your crooked heart.'

It was late  late in the evening 
   The lovers they were gone;
The clocks had ceased their chiming 
   And the deep river ran on.

main_text: What is a Wheat Allergy?A Wheat allergy is an allergic reaction to foods containing wheat.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀Did you know...- Wheat allergy is most common in babies and toddlers. It is reported that approximately 65% will grow out of their allergy by the age of 12 years.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀- Although a wheat allergy is rare in adults it is a food that will most commonly trigger a severe anaphylactic reaction.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀Wheat allergy symptoms can occur within minutes or sometimes hours of being ingested. Some allergic symptoms such as abdominal pain nausea and vomiting can also be found in coeliac disease symptoms an autoimmune disease which can make those affected by it extremely unwell. It is important to see an allergy professional for an accurate diagnosis.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀How to manage a Wheat Allergy?- Strict avoidance is critical of both wheat in foods and non-food products. Wheat can be found in surprising places such as children's play dough so it's important to check all labels.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀- Cosmetics Regulations state that all cosmetic products sold in the UK must display a complete list of ingredients. However you may find other names used for wheat confusing such as titicum vulgare or triticum aestivum.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀#wheat #wheatallergy #allergies #adultallergy #allergicreactions #intolerance #foodallergyfamily #foodsensitivities #anaphylaxisawareness #foodallergy #bloodtest #food #symptoms #health #lifestyle
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "lonmedlab"  "comment_text": "What is a Wheat Allergy?

A Wheat allergy is an allergic reaction to foods containing wheat.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Did you know...
- Wheat allergy is most common in babies and toddlers. It is reported that approximately 65% will grow out of their allergy by the age of 12 years.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
- Although a wheat allergy is rare in adults  it is a food that will most commonly trigger a severe anaphylactic reaction.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Wheat allergy symptoms can occur within minutes or sometimes hours of being ingested. Some allergic symptoms such as abdominal pain  nausea and vomiting can also be found in coeliac disease symptoms  an autoimmune disease which can make those affected by it extremely unwell. It is important to see an allergy professional for an accurate diagnosis.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
How to manage a Wheat Allergy?
- Strict avoidance is critical of both wheat in foods and non-food products. Wheat can be found in surprising places such as children's play dough so it's important to check all labels.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
- Cosmetics Regulations state that all cosmetic products sold in the UK  must display a complete list of ingredients. However  you may find other names used for wheat confusing  such as titicum vulgare or triticum aestivum.

main_text: Is bread good for you?It all depends:🍞 On the kind levitation🍞 Duration of levitation🍞 Choice of ingredients🍞 Diversity of grains salt water seeds nuts... Other ingredients...Wheat has got itself a bad name... But it is not as easy as just demonizing this popular flour.I have tried to avoid it for years... Especially l since my husband felt that he doesn't digest it well. (Still no wheat allergy or gluten sensitivity diagnosed)Frankly speaking my family still prefers conventional bread... Often unaware of the high wheat content.I m a full time working mum now... No longer I manage to look after my sourdough starters.. At least not daily.And I want to bake bread my family actually eats. Thus I made some compromises....❇️ I use wheat but allow long soaking and levitation❇️ Instead of my home made starter I use #lievitomadre... An Italian mix of sourdough starter and yeast❇️ I use 3/4 of wheat partly whole grain... But organically grown locally❇️ Diversity is key: i add more vaiaty of milled grains corn seed or shredded carrots sweet potato cooke potato or pumkin...Stay tuned: I am goint to reveal some good-to-know facts about about wheat... Maybe it is not that evil after all😜#breadbaking #wheat #brotselberbacken #belly2brain #breadporn #brotbacken #traditionalcuisine #brotbackenmachtglücklich
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "belly2brain.gutbrainchat"  "comment_text": "Is bread good for you?

It all depends:
🍞 On the kind levitation
🍞 Duration of levitation
🍞 Choice of ingredients
🍞 Diversity of grains  salt  water  seeds  nuts... Other ingredients...

Wheat has got itself a bad name... But it is not as easy as just demonizing this popular flour.

I have tried to avoid it for years... Especially l  since my husband felt  that he doesn't digest it well. (Still  no wheat allergy or gluten sensitivity diagnosed)

Frankly speaking  my family still prefers conventional bread... Often  unaware of the high wheat content.

I m a full time working mum now... No longer I manage to look after my sourdough starters.. At least not daily.

And I want to bake bread my family actually eats. Thus I made some compromises....

❇️ I use wheat  but allow long soaking and levitation
❇️ Instead of my home made starter I use #lievitomadre... An Italian mix of sourdough starter and yeast
❇️ I use 3/4 of wheat  partly whole grain... But organically grown locally
❇️ Diversity is key: i add more vaiaty of milled grains  corn  seed or shredded carrots  sweet potato  cooke potato or pumkin...

Stay tuned: I am goint to reveal some good-to-know facts about about wheat... Maybe it is not that evil after all😜

main_text: It came as a surprise to many people how much the world is dependent on Ukrainian wheat corn sunflower seeds and barley. We don’t particularly think how bread appears on our table or where biofuel comes from. Ukraine is called “the bread basket of Europe” for a reason.Right now Ukrainian ports are blocked and grains can’t get to the consumers. This isn’t the first time russian regime is using forced starvation as a weapon of genocide. Read on Holodomor and what has been happening in Ukraine in 1932-1933.I come from a culture that cherishes love for bread. If a piece of it falls to the ground you pick it up and kiss it. Out of respect.We can’t be taking even a slice of bread for granted. The fate of Ukraine is too important for the fate of the entire world.

main_text: Food Allergy Awareness WeekThis week we bring awareness to the foods that may trigger an allergic reaction.While almost any food can trigger an allergic reaction there are 9 foods that cause the majority of reactions.Here I have listed the top 6 that I have seen over the last 5 years of food testing.The other 3 include more specific categories such as all fish not just shellfish separated tree nuts from peanuts and sesame. Sesame has increased as an allergic food significantly worldwide over the last two decades. There is a current push to add sesame to the list of “ major food allergens”Many times I hear from clients “ I think it is something that I ate”. You are the expert of your own body and when you have that intuition it is most likely correct.That is where I can help and actually test your blood to see if you lack the digestive enzymes to process these foods.Which of these foods do you notice an adverse reaction?#nutritioncoach #foodallergy #essentialoils #naturalsolutions #naturalmedicine #healthierlifestyle #HealthierHumans #healthy #healthylifestyle #foodallergyawareness #foodallergy #preventativehealth #preventivecare #integrativemedicine #functionalmedicine #functionalnutrition #naturalhealth #soy #wheat #healthyhabits #shellfish #cowsmilk #natural #nuts #eggs #gluten#digestivehealth #digestiveenzymes #foodallergyawarenessweek2022 #eatfood
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "lorrizenoni"  "comment_text": "Food Allergy Awareness Week

This week we bring awareness to the foods that may trigger an allergic reaction.

While almost any food can trigger an allergic reaction  there are 9 foods that cause the majority of reactions.

Here  I have listed the top 6 that I have seen over the last 5 years of food testing.

The other 3 include more specific categories such as all fish  not just shellfish  separated tree nuts from peanuts and sesame. Sesame has increased as an allergic food significantly worldwide over the last two decades. There is a current push to add sesame to the list of “ major food allergens”

Many times I hear from clients  “ I think it is something that I ate”. You are the expert of your own body and when you have that intuition  it is most likely correct.

That is where I can help and actually test your blood to see if you lack the digestive enzymes to process these foods.

Which of these foods do you notice an adverse reaction?
